    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3262405181" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3262405181" />
    <a title="majo " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/39317215-majo"><img alt="majo " src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1577812855p2/39317215.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3262405181?book_show_action=true">Apr 18, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="majo " class="user" itemprop="url" name="majo " href="/user/show/39317215-majo">majo </a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/39317215-majo?shelf=series-im-not-going-to-finish">series-im-not-going-to-finish</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/39317215-majo?shelf=2-stars">2-stars</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/39317215-majo?shelf=year-2020">year-2020</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/39317215-majo?shelf=disappointing">disappointing</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/39317215-majo?shelf=urban-fantasy">urban-fantasy</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3262405181" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6225100821043391511">For a book aimed at children there weren&apos;t barely any in this story. The novel was about a bunch of adults, doing adult stuff and a kid wanting to have his revenge on them. And his djinni making almost all the work. <br/><br/>I was hoping to find the greatness that I found in Stroud&apos;s other series, Lockwood and co. And the truth is, I didn&apos;t find it and I&apos;m disappointed.<br/><br/>....Anyways, please go and read<a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/13555073.The_Screaming_Staircase__Lockwood___Co____1_' title='The Screaming Staircase (Lockwood &amp; Co., #1) by Jonathan Stroud' rel='nofollow noopener'>The Screaming Staircase</a>.</span>
  <span id="freeText6225100821043391511" style="display:none">For a book aimed at children there weren't barely any in this story. The novel was about a bunch of adults, doing adult stuff and a kid wanting to have his revenge on them. And his djinni making almost all the work. <br /><br />I was hoping to find the greatness that I found in Stroud's other series, Lockwood and co. And the truth is, I didn't find it and I'm disappointed.<br /><br />....Anyways, please go and read<a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/13555073.The_Screaming_Staircase__Lockwood___Co____1_" title="The Screaming Staircase (Lockwood &amp; Co., #1) by Jonathan Stroud" rel="nofollow noopener">The Screaming Staircase</a>.</span>
